5:
Man, I've really moved up in the world...
How many people wake up to a sight
like THIS?
7:
What a place for a nap, eh? I guess
I'll splurge and have another. Heck,
might as well sleep all day.
10:
If you've got time to laze around,
you've got time to help with somethin'.
Get up.
15:
Nnn, sounds like a pain, so I'll pass.
G'night...
18:
I didn't even say what I need help with
yet...
20:
C'mon, we're goin' hunting. Pantry's
out of meat.
24:
Still sounds like a pain, so I'll still pass.
I'm old and need my beauty sleep.
28:
Yeah, well, you're also gonna need
dinner. Quicker you get it over with,
the quicker I quit naggin' you.
32:
Man, I'll never get used to the whole
world-hopping thing. There's just
something about these forests.
41:
Trust me buddy. There are no people
here, and that's what makes the
difference.
43:
Sometimes, people are the real
monsters. You hear it all the time.
50:
But, hey. Doesn't hurt to give 'em
a chance. You could be a little more
trusting of folks, buddy.
56:
Yeah, you. I can tell you don't trust me.
You're still gauging whether I'm a risk
to the kids.
59:
No skin off my back, though. Heck, if it'd
give you a little peace of mind,
I wouldn't mind telling you 'boutâ€”
65:
Nah, it's just... You've got a whole
monologue prepared.
68:
Look, a guy who knows as much about
poisons as you isn't some
run-of-the-mill hunter. I get it.
70:
But you think you're the only dark and
mysterious guy we've got? I don't have
time to worry myself over each and
every one of you.
72:
I wouldn't mind sittin' through your
tragic backstory if you need an ear,
though.
76: Tch. Look at me, runnin' my mouth.
78:
One big beastie should be plenty for the
pantry, right?
82:
Looks like we finished early, so how
'bout we take a break and chat for a bit?
86:
Hah, nice shot. Now let's hear that
monologue of yours.
96:
It's my job to make sure nothing funny
happens in the forest bordering the city.
102:
More or less, yup.
Didn't used to mind it, really.
104:
But watching over adventurers from
the shadows got me thinkin'.
109:
What, you're telling me you joined us
cause you thought adventuring looked
fun? That's it?
116:
Heh. Nope. It's just funny comin' from
a guy who whines about how he's too
old for chores.
121:
Well, it's not like I can go pick up quests
from the Guild. I'm supposed to be out in
the forest working for 'em!
124:
So lemme get this straight: you've been
using us to goof off on the clock, but
then you felt guilty and decided to
'fess up?
127:
Well you don't have to put it like THAT,
but... I guess. Don't rat me out to the
kids, okay?
135:
All right, all right. So, how's the
adventuring been? Having fun?
138:
Honestly, I was just hoping for a little
change of pace. Who'dve thought I'd
end up in a whole new world?
141: It'd be impossible NOT to have fun!
